THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 211 of NRS is hereby amended by adding thereto a new
2 section to read as follows:
3 1. The sheriff, chief of police or town marshal responsible for the operation
4 of a county, city or town jail or detention facility shall develop and implement a
5 policy concerning the supervision, custody, care, security, housing and medical
6 and mental health treatment of prisoners who are transgender, gender non-
7 conforming, gender non-binary and intersex. The policy must:
8 (a) [Apply the generally accepted standards of care and best practices for the
9 supervision, custody, care, security, housing and medical and mental health
10 treatment of prisoners who are transgender, gender non-conforming, gender
11 non-binary and intersex;
12 (b)] Use respectful language and currently accepted terminology that
13 accounts for and protects the rights of prisoners who are transgender, gender
14 non-conforming, gender non-binary and intersex; [and
15 (c)] (b) Prohibit the discrimination of prisoners who are transgender, gender
16 non-conforming, gender non-binary and intersex [.] ;
17 (c) Include, or incorporate by reference, a provision which designates the
18 factors to be considered when assigning housing, which must, without limitation,
19 take into account the preference of prisoners;
20 (d) Include, or incorporate by reference, a protocol for searches, which:
21 (1) Includes considering the preference of a prisoner when determining
22 the gender of the officer assigned to conduct a search; and
23 (2) Prohibits an unclothed search for the purpose of observing the
24 genitalia of a prisoner after initial intake into the jail or detention facility, unless
25 reasonable grounds exist;
26 (e) Require medical personnel to follow the applicable standard of care when
27 treating a prisoner who is transgender, gender non-conforming, gender non-
28 binary or intersex;
29 (f) Require, to the extent practicable, that a prisoner who is transgender,
30 gender non-conforming, gender non-binary or intersex have access to preferred
31 clothing, undergarments and hygiene items, regardless of housing assignment;
32 (g) Include, or incorporate by reference, provisions that apply to adult
33 prisoners and juvenile prisoners; and
34 (h) Include, or incorporate by reference, a timely and fair grievance or
35 appeal process for any violation of the policy.
36 2. The sheriff, chief of police or town marshal responsible for the operation
37 of a county, city or town jail or detention facility may develop and implement
38 training for members of the staff of the jail or detention facility in cultural
39 competency for interacting with prisoners who are transgender, gender non-
40 conforming, gender non-binary and intersex.
41 3. Nothing in this section shall be construed to require a county, city or
42 town jail or detention facility to construct additional buildings or facilities or to
43 implement any additional training for staff to comply with a policy developed
44 pursuant to this section.
45 4. As used in this section:
46 (a) “Gender non-binary” means a person whose gender identity does not
47 conform to the traditional gender binary of male and female.

