1 (b) “Gender non-conforming” means a person whose gender characteristics
2 or behaviors do not conform to those characteristics or behaviors traditionally
3 associated with the biological sex of the person.
4 (c) “Intersex” means a condition in which a person is born with external
5 genitals, internal reproductive organs, chromosome patterns or an endocrine
6 system that does not conform to the traditional gender binary of male or female.
7 (d) “Transgender” means a person whose gender identity or expression
8 differs from the sex assigned to the person at birth.
9 Sec. 2. [The provisions of NRS 354.599 do not apply to any additional
10 expenses of a local government that are related to the provisions of this act.]
11 (Deleted by amendment.)

